race.comment: Very moderate maiden where OAK PARK MADDISON (11) gets chance. Has started five times and is city placed and stakes tested last time in as a juvenile. Solid fresh in far richer company and won't get a better chance to get off the mark. UNCOMMON MIND (7) ran on well to place two back then loomed up but couldn't go on last time. Senior rider goes on and worth another try. GAZELLE (10) placed on debut then finished fourth in the same race as UNCOMMON MIND. Has upside and expected to be in the finish. TINY BAY (5) wasn't disgraced in a richer maiden last time at Morphettville. Placed three back and in this on best figures. MIAMI MILLER (3) settled at the tail and made a bit of late ground fresh at Morphettville in a hot form race. This more suitable and fitter again can improve sharply.
